17:43.796 --> 17:45.665
* I hear tell
you're doing well *

17:45.698 --> 17:49.269
* Good things have come to you

17:49.302 --> 17:51.404
* I wish I had...

17:51.438 --> 17:54.073
[music stops]

17:56.776 --> 17:58.578
[Hope coos]

17:58.611 --> 18:01.814
* I wish I had
your good luck charm *

18:01.848 --> 18:03.550
* And you had a doo-wack-a

18:03.583 --> 18:05.352
* Doo-wack-a, doo-wack-a,
doo-wack-a *

18:05.385 --> 18:07.120
* Doo-wack-a, doo...

18:07.154 --> 18:09.589
* You're going down the street
in your big Cadillac *

18:09.622 --> 18:12.459
* You got girls in the front,
you got girls in the back *

18:12.492 --> 18:14.861
* Yeah, way in the back,
got money in the sack *

18:14.894 --> 18:17.697
* Both hands on the wheel
and your shoulders right back *

18:17.730 --> 18:20.467
* Root, doo, doo, doo,
doo, doo, doo *

18:20.500 --> 18:22.669
* I hear tell
you're doing well *

18:22.702 --> 18:25.172
* Good things have come to you

18:25.205 --> 18:27.774
* I wish I had your happiness

18:27.807 --> 18:29.776
* And you had a doo-wack-a

18:29.809 --> 18:31.378
* Doo-wack-a, doo-wack-a,
doo-wack-a *

18:31.411 --> 18:33.313
* Doo-wack-a, doo.

18:33.346 --> 18:34.914
* Doo-wack-a,
doo-wack-a... *

18:34.947 --> 18:36.849
[Maw Maw
scat singing]

18:36.883 --> 18:38.885
[Maw Maw keeps singing]

18:43.690 --> 18:45.625
How about that?

18:45.658 --> 18:47.360
I like it.

18:47.394 --> 18:48.895
Sure you do.

18:48.928 --> 18:51.298
It's another crazy thing
to make fun of our family about.

18:51.331 --> 18:52.699
You want to go
in the other room

18:52.732 --> 18:54.367
and have a look at my
grandmother's inverted nipples?

18:54.401 --> 18:56.203
How about our
bank statement?

18:56.236 --> 18:57.470
That's a hoot.

18:57.504 --> 18:59.872
I think it's a great picture.

18:59.906 --> 19:01.774
I mean, my family has
all those portraits

19:01.808 --> 19:03.910
that you were talking about,
and, you know,

19:03.943 --> 19:06.413
we're all smiling, but
somebody told us when to smile,

19:06.446 --> 19:08.748
so those smiles are fake.

19:08.781 --> 19:10.483
All these smiles are real.

19:12.485 --> 19:14.587
You captured a moment
of actual family joy,

19:14.621 --> 19:16.889
and that's kind of rare.

19:18.458 --> 19:21.394
I think you finally
got your picture.

19:25.232 --> 19:27.200
I like her, Jimmy.

19:27.234 --> 19:30.570
Smart, insightful.

19:30.603 --> 19:32.839
I told you
we had a lot in common.

19:32.872 --> 19:34.241
You're staying for dinner.

19:34.274 --> 19:37.410
We've having TV dinners!

19:37.444 --> 19:38.911
[phone ringing]
If you're a vegetarian,

19:38.945 --> 19:40.980
I'm pretty sure you can
talk Burt into trading you

19:41.013 --> 19:43.216
his vegetable section

19:43.250 --> 19:45.818
for your Salisbury
steak section.

19:45.852 --> 19:47.654
She hit ignore.

19:47.687 --> 19:49.222
What?
She hit ignore.

19:49.256 --> 19:50.523
Her boyfriend just called,
and she hit ignore.

19:50.557 --> 19:51.791
What does that mean?

19:51.824 --> 19:53.293
My phone doesn't have
an ignore.

19:53.326 --> 19:54.894
When I ignore someone,
I just ignore them.

19:54.927 --> 19:56.563
I don't know. I don't
have ignore, either.

19:56.596 --> 19:57.764
But this is
good, right?

19:57.797 --> 20:00.400
Go kiss her.
What?!

20:00.433 --> 20:02.602
Go kiss her. Now.
It's time. I'm telling you.

20:02.635 --> 20:05.405
You need to do it
before it's too late. Go!

20:07.274 --> 20:08.575
Two pounds, three ounces.

20:08.608 --> 20:10.677
Mother is resting comfortably.

20:12.679 --> 20:14.447
Thanks for having me over.

20:14.481 --> 20:16.449
This was really fun.
[chuckles nervously]

20:17.917 --> 20:19.586
[no audible dialogue]

20:21.354 --> 20:23.656
I, uh, I gotta admit
I was a little nervous

20:23.690 --> 20:25.392
about you learning so much
about my family.

20:25.425 --> 20:26.726
I thought it might
scare you off.

20:26.759 --> 20:27.894
Oh, no way.

20:27.927 --> 20:29.028
No, just the opposite.

20:29.061 --> 20:31.898
[both chuckle]

20:31.931 --> 20:34.434
However, if you meet a
girl that you want to date,

20:34.467 --> 20:36.469
you know, like,
not just a friend?

20:36.503 --> 20:38.338
You might want to hold off
on showing her

20:38.371 --> 20:39.839
the family photo album
for a couple months.

20:39.872 --> 20:42.775
Yeah, that might be
a good idea.
Yeah.

20:42.809 --> 20:45.478
Waited too long...

20:45.512 --> 20:47.514
just like Ross.

20:48.715 --> 20:50.550
She's... [grunts]

20:50.583 --> 20:52.619
[both chuckle]

20:52.652 --> 20:56.389
JIMMY:
Maybe I did wait too long.

20:56.423 --> 20:58.858
But I did learn
one thing today:

20:58.891 --> 21:00.493
Sabrina likes me.

21:00.527 --> 21:02.762
Right now it might just be
as a friend,

21:02.795 --> 21:04.697
but who knows?

21:04.731 --> 21:06.966
[Hope cooing]

21:06.999 --> 21:09.436
She was enjoying hanging out
with me enough

21:09.469 --> 21:11.304
to ignore a call
from her boyfriend.

21:11.338 --> 21:14.507
Maybe one day she'll be willing
to ignore him altogether.

21:14.541 --> 21:16.509
[cooing]

21:20.513 --> 21:22.915
Shh...

21:26.018 --> 21:28.388
[Hope crying]

21:28.421 --> 21:30.089
Yep,

21:30.122 --> 21:33.760
I thought that was
a little too easy. All right.

21:36.028 --> 21:37.730
CHILD: Adios, amigos.

21:37.764 --> 21:38.831
Thanks for watchin'.
